      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-09-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2022-04-21T14:28:28Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Rural Opioid Abuse Prevention Act</strong></p> <p>This bill expands the allowable uses of grant funds under the Comprehensive Opioid, Stimulant, and Substance Abuse Program administered by the Department of Justice.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill allows grants to be used for pilot programs for rural areas to implement community response programs that focus on alternatives to incarceration and reducing opioid overdose deaths.</p> <p>The bill also requires at least 10% of grants under the program to be awarded to rural areas.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
